# TB Pro Theme Ticket Expansions

**Every theme visualization row** must be expandable to ticket IDs — no exceptions.

Applies to: long-close themes, Flight 2 themes, all-launch leaderboard, misdirected, any `.theme-row` block.
## Ticket line format — paraphrased, not raw

Each ticket line: **`#ID` link + paraphrased generic theme description** — never raw Zendesk subject, never ID-only.

Lisa confirmed: *"general idea of ticket is good so people know what they want to click."*

- **English:** short paraphrase (e.g. `#6125 — Payment processing delay`).
- **Non-English:** paraphrase + `*(Language — "translation")*`.
- **`.eng-card__subject`:** same rule — paraphrased labels, not API subjects.

**Generator:** paraphrase at build time in `tbpro_launch_overview.py` — never embed raw Zendesk subjects in committed HTML.

**Footer:** *"Ticket subjects paraphrased; non-English quotes include AI translations."* — not "PII-redacted" unless that step ran.

## Required HTML pattern

Wrap each theme in `.theme-row-wrap`. The bar/count row stays in `.theme-row`; ticket list goes in `<details class="theme-tickets">`:

```html
<div class="theme-row-wrap">
  <div class="theme-row">…name, count, bar…</div>
  <details class="theme-tickets">
    <summary>N tickets</summary>
    <ul class="theme-tickets__list">
      <li>
        <a href="https://tbpro.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/{id}" target="_blank">#{id}</a>
        <span class="theme-tickets__subj"> — paraphrased theme description</span>
        <span class="theme-tickets__gh"><a href="…">repo#issue</a></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </details>
</div>
```

- Link format: `https://tbpro.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/{id}`
- Summary count must match list length (`summary` text ↔ `<li>` count).

## Data source & common mistakes

Re-fetch Zendesk (`fetch_tickets()` / `classify_ticket()` in `tbpro_launch_overview.py`; `zd_search_all()` in `tbpro_daily.py`) before embedding lists. Do not hardcode stale IDs or paste raw subjects.

Reference: `lisa/daily/launch_overview_sample.html`.
